Look at the following description corresponding the the relavant image(s), Then answer a question

***Start of description***

The image shows a Lewis structure of a molecule or ion. The central atom is bonded to four other atoms, each represented by a circle with a pair of dots (representing lone pairs of electrons) on either side. The arrangement of these atoms around the central atom forms a square planar geometry. Each corner of the square represents one of the bonded atoms, and the central atom is at the intersection of the lines connecting these corners.

***End of description***
Now, answer the question:

Choose the word that best describes the geometric shape of the molecule or ion whose Lewis structure is shown below. <image 1>

A. linear
B. bent
C. triangular planar
D. tetrahedral
E. square planar
F. triangular pyramid
G. triangular bipyramid
H. octahedral
I. T-shape

Based on the description provided, the Lewis structure shows a central atom bonded to four other atoms arranged in a square planar geometry. Therefore, the geometric shape of the molecule or ion is best described as "square planar."

So, the answer is:

E. square planar
